[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Introduction"]
[Black "The First Game of Chess"]
[Result "*"]

{ The first-ever game played in our noble sport was as early as 1475 and it actually featured the king's pawn opening! }
1. e4 d5
{ I was very surprised to find that the Black player replied with the Scandinavian defense in this historically relevant game! }
2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd8
{ It took the Black side almost another 400 years to find the strongest queen move - Qa5 and 500 years to find the second strongest queen move - Qd6. }
4. Bc4 Nf6 5. Nf3 Bg4 { It was a pity that Bxf7+ was missed here! } 6. h3
{ White went on to win the game in @@StartBracket@@De Castellvi-Vinoles Valencia 1475@@EndBracket@@. This game possibly kick-started the first move advantage which continues to this day :@@EndBracket@@! }
