[White "Introduction"]
[Black "My Personal Experience"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4
{ My mom taught me chess at the age of 6, and now 24  years later I get the chance to dedicate my second Chessable course to her.  She continues to teach me in ways I could only dream of! I kept telling her...  once I finish my Lifetimes repertoires on 1.e4, I will become a master of this line.I hope to honor my word and I wish the viewers to join me on this journey to understand the opening used by the greatest players of all time! I  have tried almost all of the first moves including 1.f4 :@@EndBracket@@ ...but nothing compares to the results I have achieved using 1.e4 with a cool 67.1% statistics in Mega database, not even my recent favorite 1.b3 :@@EndBracket@@ which has only 65%! }
