{ White has tried other knight retreats to d3 and c4, but frankly it can hardly challenge Black...If he knows what he is doing! }
4... Nxe4 5. Nc3
{ Don Fabi was pretty much unstoppable during Berlin Candidates 2018...there was only one person who could stop him delivering him the only defeat in the event, It was none other than Sergey Karjakin - the previous challenger for the World Championship. He used this line and created an absolute masterpiece! }
5... Nf6
{ This lame retreat is not recommended and we can achieve an easy edge with simple means. }
6. d4 { Capturing the center. One day our extra tempo will be useful for us. }
6... g6
{ This option of fianchetto is pretty decent and has been played by Kuzubov and Fridman. }
7. Bc4
{ An epic direction introduced into practice by Nils Grandelius, who is known for his theoretical prowess. }
7... Bg7
{ Black is hoping that we won't deliver the punishment for taking his own time to develop his bishop via the fianchetto! }
8. Qe2+ { An important check stopping Black from castling into safety. } 8...
Qe7
{ Allowing the queens to remain while also losing the castling rights is not something you want! }
9. Qxe7+ Kxe7 10. O-O
{ With a big advantage thanks to Black's weak king and threats like Nb5/Ng5, we make full use of our lead in development. }
