10... Re8 11. Ng5
{ Introduced into practice by Fressinet way back in 2004 and it is a shame that no GM or even IM has repeated this epic move! Once again it is my wish that my course changes that and people start playing this move. }
11... Bf6 { was the reaction of two of Fressinet's opponents. } 12. Bc4
{ Targetting the vulnerable f7-point. Black's situation is already hopeless! }
12... Be6
{ Hoping to reduce the firepower by exchanging some minor pieces.   12...Ne6  was seen in the blitz game between @@StartBracket@@Fressinet-Petrosian Blitz 2004@@EndBracket@@.  13.g4!  N  leading to a strong attacking position with a big advantage, since our attack has already reached overwhelming proportions while Black's queenside army is happily sleeping :@@EndBracket@@. }
13. Nxe6
{ Sadly parting with the knight... but achieving a big advantage using the might of the bishop pair! }
13... Nxe6 14. Be3
{ No way we are giving up the bishop pair, the plan is to continue with f4, g4, or h5 all moves work well depending on Black's move. Comp already gives a big advantage since he doesn't see any counterplay for Black. }
