{ Due to the provocation, we can indulge ourselves in the pawn grabbing operation with h3-g4 since we might lose the d3-pawn or allow Black to gain the initiative. }
9. Nbd2
{ Strictly following the principles of the Italian. The knight will go to e4 or f1 and kick the enemy bishop out of the pin on the d1-h5 diagonal. }
9... O-O 10. a4
{ A nice move to prepare the retreat of the bishop and a5 gaining more space over the queenside. We have the advantage here due to our pressure on the e5-pawn. }
