8... Nb6 { I tried to see what would happen after this natural move. } 9. Bb3
{ Funnily the bishop doesn't have much role to play from both b3 or c2, but If we have to agree to one of those...I think on b3, It is slightly more active. }
9... e5 { Closing the position. } 10. Be3
{ Preparing Qd2 next with ideas of queenside castling. } 10... Ne8
{ Black is trying to play like the typical "Kings-Indian" player. } 11. Qd2
{ Continuing to implement our strategy for playing for opposite side castling. }
11... f5 { This is premature with our king's position not defined yet. } 12.
exf5 { Opening the position. } 12... gxf5 13. Bg5
{ A nice tempo gaining a move to prevent f4. } 13... Qc7 14. O-O-O
{ With a big advantage as we can easily breakthrough in the kingside by preparing g4 ideas while it might take Black a long time to get something going on in the queenside. }
