{ I think we can make a footnote that g6 systems in the Bd7 have to be met with Rb1 followed by preparation of the b4-break to gain play on the queenside.   8...e6  9.Ne1!  followed by f4-Nf3 next with a cool initiative on the kingside, while Black is still struggling to find a good plan of counter-attack. After f4, we also can continue with Qf3-h3 to increase our influence and strengthen our attack by including the queen. }
9. Rb1
{ This is how we create a play and destroy the potential of the fianchetto bishop. }
