{ This has the stamp of approval as the best line for Black.   5...Nc6  will transpose to 4...Nc6 lines.   5...a6  6.Bxd7+  Nbxd7  7.O-O  will transpose to 4...a6 lines. }
6. Bxd7+
{ The right time to take on d7 and then choose our plans depending on how Black will recapture the bishop. }
6... Qxd7
{ In the fianchetto systems, it is better to recapture with the queen to develop the b8-knight to c6 fighting for the central square on d4. }
7. d4 { Just in time before Black can play Nc6 stopping our main concept. }
7... cxd4 8. Qxd4
{ This has been featured in 8 games, while the mainline with Nxd4 has been played in more than 1100 games! The knight on f3 is quite decently placed, so why not improve the activity of the queen? The queen always has a nice retreat square on d3 where it keeps an eye on both the e4 and c4 pawns. }
8... Bg7
{ Black is trying to play without Nc6 to have the idea to play an early Rc8. }
9. O-O O-O
{ Black has defined his setup and is waiting for us to do the same.   9...Nc6  10.Qd3  will  transpose to 7...Nc6 lines. }
10. Bg5 { Trying to provoke h6 which will weaken the kingside. } 10... Nc6
{ Here we have to be slightly precise to make sure that Black doesn't get any active ideas. }
11. Qd2
{ This was made possible due to our last move! The queen is slightly better placed on d2 compared to d3 in the current situation to avoid Ng4-e5 ideas. }
11... Qe6 { A nice double attack on e4 and c4. } 12. Qe2 { Double defense!! }
12... h6
{ Black won't feel the effect of this move right now, but we must make sure that he will live to regret making this move at some point in the game!! }
13. Bd2
{ We have managed to keep the stability of the position while at the same time retaining our positional trumps of better space and fewer piece exchanges. The bishop protects the c3-knight to enable b3 move without having to worry about the c3-knight. }
13... Rac8 14. b3
{ Overprotecting c4 after which we can continue with Rad1 and Rfe1 with a nice Maroczy Bind. Black has to play moves like g5 to create some play, but even that is not enough to equalize here. }
