3... e5
{ This line which is a decent choice against @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.e4  c5  2.Nf3  Nc6  3.Nc3  is just bad here, as we haven't developed the knight to c3 giving rise to ideas involving c3-d4 capturing the center. }
4. O-O Be7
{ A necessary move to prevent Ng5 ideas.   4...Nf6  would allow a devastating move for White.  5.Ng5  and the f7-pawn shall fall or Black has to open the position with d5 without being fully ready for that. }
5. d4
{ You just gotta love it, when you can sacrifice a pawn for getting the initiative. }
5... exd4
{ 5...cxd4  6.c3  Forcing the opening of the position.  6...Nf6  7.cxd4  and Black better transpose back  7...exd4  8.e5  Ng4  transposing to the mainline. }
6. c3
{ Black can't take on c3 with  6...dxc3  due to  7.Qd5  winning on the spot due to the unstoppable threat of Qxf7+. }
6... Nf6
{ Black gives back the pawn to finish his development before things can get ugly. }
7. e5 { Forcing the knight to abandon his safe pathways and enter the jungle! }
7... Ng4 8. cxd4 { This inclusion of cxd4 favors us. } 8... cxd4
{ The d-pawn has already become a backward pawn. } 9. Re1
{ Activating the rook and protecting our key central pawn on e5. } 9... d6
{ Ensuring the safe return for the knight.   9...d5  is not the same as we can avoid  exd6  .  10.Bb3!  We will back the pawn on d4 with interest, and also, the knight on g4 will require some care after we play h3. }
10. exd6 Qxd6
{ Black just needs one more move to be completely fine with O-O next. } 11. h3
{ Kicking the knight away and making a 'Luft' for our king. } 11... Nf6 12. Nc3
{ Playing with great energy and using the fact that Black can't take on c3 due to Qxd6 utilizing the pin along the e-file thanks to the king on e8. }
12... O-O { The safer choice not trying to retain the pawn. } 13. Nb5 Qc5
{ Black has to take up the gauntlet as the natural retreat to d8 would allow Bf4 with a powerful initiative thanks to the control of the h2-b8 diagonal. }
14. b3
{ Protecting the bishop on c4 followed by Ba3 next with a slight pull as the queen on c5 looks funny and we will regain the d4-pawn with more active pieces. }
