{ Creating a central bind with this powerful center pawn hook. } 8... Nd5 9.
Bb3
{ With c4 next, we have a big advantage due to Black's very backward pawn on d7, and our queen can go to g4 to create attacking chances on the kingside. Our b1-knight can be developed via d2-e4/c4. }
