3... e6
{ Black is preparing a quick d5 to punish and utilize our early bishop sortie. }
4. O-O Nf6 { Black is trying to provoke us into playing e5. } 5. Re1
{ The most natural move, developing the rook and fighting against Black's d5-break. I feel this is more challenging than  5.d3  . }
5... d5 { is premature and gives us the advantage without any troubles. } 6.
exd5 Nxd5 7. d4
{ Capturing the center and after the exchange of the d-pawn for the c5-pawn, we will have the queenside majority and better development leading to a solid advantage in the middlegame. }
