1... c5
{ The Sicilian Defense: The answer for all the living beings who aren't satisfied with just equalizing and want to fight for the full point against any form of opposition! }
2. Nf3
{ Although I have had my fair share of fun with the Alapin and the Closed Sicilian with  2.Nc3  , when I want to decimate my opponents this is the move I resort to! }
2... e6
{ Black prefers to keep the diagonal of the f8-bishop open compared to the usual d6 systems where Black's priority is the light-squared bishop. Hence we can conclude that Black is adopting a dark-squared strategy. }
3. b3
{ Throwing caution to the winds! This Cowboy move is sure to throw your opponents off balance as they will be expecting  3.d4  ,  3.c3  , or even  3.g3  but they will never be ready for this :@@EndBracket@@ !!With this, I am paying homage to my very first Chessable course where I managed to pull off a Lifetime Repertoire with 1.b3. One of the biggest advantages of systems involving b3 is that Black players can never take it seriously which gives us very good chances to gain the advantage or a fighting initiative. Just put on the classic cowboy theme from ' The good, the bad and the ugly' when working on this line and everything will work fine :@@EndBracket@@! }
3... d5 { Capturing the center, though this line can't challenge our concept. }
4. Bb5+
{ This early check without the inclusion of exd5 is the ideal move order as it reduces Black's options. }
4... Bd7 5. Bxd7+ Nxd7 { This natural recapture is already a mistake! } 6. exd5
{ Opening the e-file as we are able to get the king's rook to e1 in two moves! }
6... exd5 7. O-O
{ After this Black is in trouble due to his poor development which is going to make sure that he can't comfortably place his pieces to his liking. }
7... Ngf6
{ This or Be7 are very similar and will eventually transpose to the same lines after Re1. }
8. Re1+
{ The mighty rook is here to mess with the coordination of Black's forces. }
8... Be7
{ Black just needs one more move to castle and he can be happy with the outcome of the opening... }
9. Qe2
{ Stopping that from happening and we are clearly better thanks to the pin along the e-file which makes sure that Black can't castle. We can continue with Bb2 or even Ba3 in some lines to increase pressure against Black's position. }
