O-O-O
{ Protecting the c5-pawn and hoping that the king will be safe on the queenside. }
10. d4 { Changing the pawn structure to our favor. } 10... cxd4
{ Hoping to exchange some material to equalize the pressure. } 11. b4
{ A powerful pawn sacrifice threatening b5 next... Black can't accept due to Qxd4 with triple attack on b4, a7, and g7. }
