Nxd4 { Once the d-pawn is off, the weakness on d6 starts to make itself felt! }
6... Nf6
{ This move doesn't work since Black is not ready for the opening for the position. }
7. Nxc6
{ Asking Black to choose between two depressing options: 1. Play a worse endgame with passive play 2. Play a worse middlegame with dubious play. Hard choice :@@EndBracket@@. }
7... bxc6
{ 7...dxc6  8.Qxd8  Kxd8  9.Bf4  followed by O-O-O next with a big advantage as the Black king will never find his peace in this game. }
8. e5 { GO BACK! } 8... Ng8 { The knight's journey was 'Short and Sweet'. } 9.
Bf4
{ Strengthening our stronghold on e5. We can pursue our development with Bd3 followed by O-O with a clear advantage. }
