{ An intermediate shot that Black always has to watch out for in this early Bb5 exchange line. }
7... Bxc5 8. b4
{ Black won't have the time to take on f2 as the bishop will then meet an early death. }
8... Bxf2+
{ Black has to take the pawn otherwise, his whole opening concept doesn't make any sense. }
9. Kf1
{ At the cost of weakening our king permanently, we won the fight for the initiative! }
9... Bd7
{ Shirov chose this move in a rapid game and here White missed the chance to gain the decisive advantage with a powerful idea. }
10. c4
{ Preparing to win the piece with c5 and Black can't afford to let that happen despite getting three pawns in return as his dark-square weaknesses will lead to his doom! }
10... dxc4 { No other alternative for Black. } 11. Na3
{ Black will suffer heavy material losses due to the dual threat of Nc4-d6 and attacking the queen making her lose the support of the bishop on f2. White had the advantage and went on to win smoothly in  @@StartBracket@@Yemelin-Sharankov 2009@@EndBracket@@. }
