{ A strong novelty that changes the evaluation of the line permanently. Black's entire concept lies in the fact whether the f2-bishop will survive or not and we use that very point to continue improving our position on the queenside by threatening the deadly a5 which will force Black to lose his bishop on f2. }
10... a5
{ Looks like the natural retort, but allows White to execute another interesting idea which gives him the advantage. }
11. Qd2
{ Controlling the key e3-square and preparing to win the f2-bishop by moving the e2-bishop to d3 or d1. }
11... Nh6 12. Bd3
