Bc3
{ An interesting concept... Our knight does look silly on a4, but it can never be targeted by Black due to the threat of Nc5 changing the pawn structure in our favor. }
12... b5
{ Asking for trouble :@@EndBracket@@ . This move was played by Korchnoi.   13.Bxb5  will be met with  13...Nxe5  . }
13. Nc5
{ This move is stronger, deviating from the Korchnoi game where his opponent took on b5 allowing Black to equalize after the tactical trick with Nxe5 regaining the pawn. }
13... Bxc5 14. dxc5
{ I wonder how the legend would have continued here... as I feel it is a very difficult position for Black due to the passive nature. }
14... b4 { Forcing the bishop to reduce the support of the e5-pawn. } 15. Bd2
Qb8 { Black is going after the recently weakened e5-pawn. } 16. Bd3
{ This is clearly better for White since Black can't on e5 due to Bxf5 ideas. }
