6. Be2
{ I felt this was the easiest way to gain the advantage without any hurdles! }
6... cxd4 7. cxd4 Bb5
{ Black has achieved his life's ambition...but at what cost? } 8. Nc3
{ White has many ways to get the advantage, but I feel this is the simplest and strongest. Asking Black to take on e2 and we will take back with the knight which will eventually go to f4-h5 to put Black's king safety in jeopardy. }
8... Bb4
{ Trying to be very clever and using the fact that our king is on e1 to create a pin. }
9. O-O { Now the threat to take on b5 is real! } 9... Bxc3 10. Bxb5+
{ Forcing Black'squeen to b5 which will help us, when we give a crucial tempo by attacking the queen to bring the c1-bishop to a3 under such favorable circumstances. }
10... Qxb5 11. bxc3
{ The slightly weak pawn on c3 shouldn't concern us, since the advantages derived from it like the open b-file, the solo bishop on c1 which will be unmatched in the fight for dark-square control are the more important factors that give us a big advantage. }
11... Ne7 { Hoping to castle quickly. } 12. a4
{ As I said earlier, we gain a tempo and get the bishop to a3 with a big advantage since Black still needs two moves to finish his development. }
