8... Bxe2 9. Nxe2
{ Although the exchange has favored Black, the time lost and the fact that we can easily organize play against the Black king with Nf4-h5 guarantees a big advantage. }
9... Ne7
{ The knight wants to go to f5 or c6. Though on f5 it is a target for our g-pawn and on c6 it is not doing anything apart from getting in the way of the b8-knight. }
10. O-O
{ Calm before the storm! It is important to castle before embarking on our plans since there will be annoying Bb4+ or Qa6 if we move the knight from e2 stopping us from castling. }
10... Nec6 11. Rb1
{ A useful prophylaxis freeing the c1-bishop and planning to expand with b4 when the time is right. White had the advantage and converted confidently in  @@StartBracket@@Svidler-Gelfand 2006@@EndBracket@@. }
