7. O-O Ng6 8. Be3
{ Developing the bishop to enable Nbd2 next and our super setup is complete! I didn't fully like Gawain's recommendation with  8.g3  which ironically was also my first intention :@@EndBracket@@, I found that Black has a way to gain a tenable position with good chances to equalize...while I failed to find the same against our mainline with 8.Be3.Although the bishop looks passive at the moment, in the future the d4-pawn is likely to be a target and we are already making preparations for the middlegame battle! }
8... Be7
{ Black doesn't have many ways to continue here, either he can do Be7 directly or with the inclusion of 8...cxd4 which will most transpose to our mainlines at some point. }
9. Nbd2
{ Our configuration is ready! We can continue building our position with Re1-Bd3 with a very nice play in the center and kingside. }
9... O-O
{ Black is finally ready to play f6 at some point... but the question is 'Will that be enough for achieving equality?' }
10. a3 { Preparing to gain even more space with b4 next. } 10... a5
{ Black is not going to give us any help and instead fights against our plans. }
11. Bd3
{ Discouraging any funny breaks due to the threat of Bxg6 ruining Black's pawn structure. I am not saying this is the main way, but just an option to be considered seriously. }
