{ Starting to act like the material is equal and continue to mobilize our forces! Be warned - Black's defensive resources are not to be underestimated! We will need every member of our army to go all out in this fight between Good vs evil :@@EndBracket@@. }
8... Nge7
{ Thanks to the powerful pawn hook on e5, Black's knight can be activated either via e7 or g6. }
9. h4
{ AlphaZero's favorite pawn plunge designed to create another attacking pawn hook! Black is unfortunately faced with a difficult decision of allowing the pawn to h5 or h6 or stop it with h5 which would seriously compromise his king safety and the f7-weak point after an eventual knight jump to g5 followed by Qf3 laying waste to f7. }
9... Rc8
{ This move has one obvious drawback - abandoning the long castling option. Black's king now has to sit in the center or get checkmated by our overwhelming army if he goes to the kingside! }
10. Nbd2
{ I feel this is more dangerous and stronger than Gawain's recommendation with  10.h5  which I feel allows Black to liquidate after the prophylactic  10...h6  . }
10... Qc7
{ The Black queen is visionary and predicts that the b-file is going to be opened very soon with Nb3. When that happens he is expecting Rb1 and hence it seems like a wise decision to go Qc7 immediately. }
11. h5 { This is the ideal time to extend our initiative using the h-pawn. }
11... h6 { Stopping h6 ideas. } 12. Qe2
{ With full compensation as we can cooly continue with Nb3 and Rb1, while the black king is destined to stay in the center as he will be ruthlessly hunted with ideas like g4-g5 if he tries to be brave by going short castling. }
