{ This advancing move is most dangerous as Black has only one accurate way to get to 0.00 :@@EndBracket@@. }
10... Rc8
{ This safe waiting move is Black's best bet. He wants to see how we will proceed and only then choose his plans.   10...a6  willtranspose to  9...a6 10.h5 h6 lines. }
11. Na3 { Threatening future Nb5 ideas. } 11... Nf5
{ The strongest response opening the a3-f8 diagonal and increasing the influence on the d4-square. }
12. g4 Nfe7 { Taking on c3 only helps White. } 13. Nb5
{ The following line is forced for both sides with no deviation! } 13... Nxe5
{ The only way to prevent Nd6+ and Nxd4. Black uses the fact that we have less protection for the b5-knight. }
14. Nxe5
{ Other moves would lead to positions with no compensation :@@EndBracket@@. }
14... Bxb5 15. Qf3
{ We can't afford to make any soft moves and must continue in the same sacrificial spirit! }
15... f6 { The f7-point was threatened and this was the only defense. } 16.
Bg6+ { Changing the character of the position. } 16... Nxg6 17. Nxg6
{ The knight is looking well-posted on g6. } 17... Rg8
{ The only other alternative with  17...Rh7  loses to  18.a4!  Followed by Qxd5 with a winning attack. }
18. Bxh6 { Destroying Black's pawn shelter. } 18... gxh6
{ Once again Black has to agree to whatever we are throwing at him :@@EndBracket@@. }
19. Qxf6 { The e6-point is about to fall. } 19... Bd7
{ The bishop returns to safeguard the king. The other defense with  19...Rc6  fails to  20.Rad1  with all of our pieces joining in the final winning assault. }
20. Re5
{ Freeing the path for the next rook to join with Re1 ganging up against the e6-pawn which is Black's last line of defense. }
20... dxc3
{ This greedy move is very difficult to find! Other moves lose to Rae1. } 21.
Rae1 c2
{ Queening on  c1  is the safest for Black.  21...cxb2  loses to  22.Rxe6+  and we will eventually win the b2-pawn with a queen check on f6. }
22. Nxf8
{ Only here does Black has a decent alternative with Rxg4+ which also leads to a draw. }
22... Rxf8 { The safest. } 23. Rxe6+ Qxe6
{ Taking with the bishop will also lead to the same. } 24. Rxe6+ Bxe6 25. Qxe6+
{ With a draw by repetition after Kd8 Qd6+. Black only managed to survive due to the mighty pawn on c2. }
