{ Taking back what was rightfully ours, the center!   6.Nxf6+  gxf6  7.g3  Nb4  8.d3  Qd5!  @@StartBracket@@threatening to take on c2 and f3@@EndBracket@@  9.Bg2  Bg4  and White will lose by pawn due to the pin along the h5-d1 & a8-h1 diagonal combined with the threat of distraction with Nxc2. }
6... Qd5 7. Nc3
{ Continuing our policy of avoiding exchanges, as we have the space advantage. }
7... Qa5 8. Ne5
{ The knight occupies the powerful central post on e5 which can't be challenged by the a6 knight who is starting to wonder what he is doing there :@@EndBracket@@ . }
8... Nb4 9. a3 Be6 10. g3
{ A simple and strong idea, preparing to fianchetto the bishop with the idea to castle next. Black is still struggling with his space issues and limited activity for his pieces. }
