{ Avoiding the doubling of the pawns as taking back with the g-pawn, while weakening the h7-pawn was never in Black's plan! }
6. Qxe4
{ This is an annoying position for Black, he has many ways to fight for equality...but none of them fully does the job! }
6... Qa5 { Black is preparing Bf5 to annoy our well-placed queen. } 7. b4
{ Black was asking for it! } 7... Qd5
{ Black argues that the move b4 weakens the a1-h8 diagonal which helps him in some lines. Question: Do we care? Answer: We don't! There are bigger things in life than such subtleties :@@EndBracket@@! }
8. Qe3
{ Envisioning the futuristic queen exchange where we can recapture with the f-pawn following another golden principle of 'Capturing towards the center'. It is important to note that now 8.Qh4 is not as strong, since the inclusion of b4 has weakened our position and doesn't allow some ideas. }
8... Bf5 9. c4
{ Continuing to use the momentum provided the queen to gain more space and control over the position. }
9... Qe4 10. Be2
{ Breaking the pin and threatening to avoid the queen exchange with Qc3 next. }
10... Qxe3 11. fxe3
{ with a very pleasant endgame advantage as we can improve on our expansion plans on the queenside while also laughing at Black's 'No idea in life nor game'. }
