{ Followed by c4 kicking the d5-knight which will enable us to place our c1-bishop on f4 which cuts into Black's territory and gets in the way of his coordination. The a1-rook will reach his destined place on d1 and we can soften Black's kingside setup with the AlphaZero style h4-h5 which is a key defect of the fianchetto setup! }
