8. Bd3 { Ignoring it and continuing with our plans. } 8... Nxg3 9. fxg3
{ This is the killer idea! White completely abandons his d4-pawn and also voluntarily ruins his kingside pawn structure to open up the f-file! }
9... cxd4 10. O-O
{ Material is not important, 'Development and initiative is the priority!' }
10... Nc6 11. Qe2 { Protecting e5-pawn and preparing the deadly Ng5 jump. }
11... h6 { Allowing Ng5 would seal the deal for Black. } 12. a3
{ After this prophylactic move, Black has no active plans left and can only sadly watch while we improve our position! If comp gives such a huge advantage despite being a pawn down, then obviously it is bad news for Black. Our plans involve b4-Bd2 on the queenside and g4 on the kingside with complete domination, while the Black king will be ruthlessly hunted wherever he goes! }
