{ The Caro-Kann Defense is one of my personal favorites as I scored a memorable 23-move victory over Kryvoruchko Yuri. This opening is named after the English player Horatio Caro and the Austrian player Marcus Kann, who analyzed it in 1886. It was a significant moment in its history and marked the beginning of this solid opening which can be molded according to the preference of the player!It is an opening that can be played and mastered by both aggressive/positional players. Do not be fooled by its appearance, many great players have fallen victim to it :@@EndBracket@@. Erwin's epic course was one of my earliest relationships with Chessable. Although I loved it with all my heart, I had to fight my personal feelings to find a clear way to advantage. In the end, I think I managed to do the impossible and cracked Erwin's bulletproof analysis! }
