2. d4
{ The best move, I had also tried the enterprising  2.Nc3  with the idea to meet  2...e5  3.f4  taking the game to King's Gambit type positions which many of the Philidor fans won't like. I think it is a good alternative to research for interested readers! }
2... Nf6 3. Nc3
{ Although  3.Bd3  was a tempting option to continue with  3...e5  4.d5  .  In the end, I decided we needn't avoid the mainstream theory and go for the mainlines with my guided approach! }
