{ Black is preparing the retreat of the bishop to f8, though in principle such a slow plan can hardly bother us.   7...Nc6  This is just downright bad as it allows us to weaken Black's pawn structure permanently.  8.Nxc6  bxc6  9.O-O  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/ppp1bppp/3p1n2/8/3NP3/2N3P1/PPP2P1P/R1BQKB1R b KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6...Nc6  lines. See the comments on how the play might continue in that line.   7...c6  8.O-O  One of our main concepts is to play b3 followed by Bb2 and then proceed to squeeze Black into submission.  8...Re8  9.h3  with a transposition to 8...c6 lines. }
