{ Black's plan consists of c6-b5 and trying to create play against the e4-pawn. }
9. Re1
{ Always remember that in this fianchetto edition of the Philidor, overprotecting the e4-pawn is always a good idea to destroy Black's hopes of counterplay. And since we can release any of the piece's duty of passively defending the e4-pawn, we can suddenly shift the roles of the pieces aggressively to attack Black's weakness. }
9... Nbd7
{ The knight is coming to c5 to put pressure on the e4-pawn.   9...c6  transposes to 8...c6lines. }
10. a4
{ Already starting to fight against Black's aforementioned expansion plans with c6-b5. }
