{ Always a cool precaution against any future Ng4/Bg4 ideas and also preparing the invasive g4 plans. }
11... a5
{ 11...Nc5  12.b3  followed by Bb2 and our piece placement could be Qd2, Rad1, and Re3 if needed with a pleasant advantage. }
12. b3
{ The cowboy move! Preparing to put the bishop on the long diagonal where it will be at his strongest. }
12... Nc5 13. Bb2 { Fianchetto bishop is a happy bishop! } 13... g6
{ Black is preparing to challenge our b2-bishop with his own sniper. } 14. Qf3
{ Followed by Rad1 next with a full bind on the position as most of Black's plans have been neutralized. }
