{ Deviating from Sethu's direction. He has recommended 5.Qd2 followed by f4, while I am more in favor of quick kingside development with Nf3. Practically this feels more dangerous as we are not making any weakness and preparing the central e5 advance if Black is not careful. }
5... h6 { Forcing us to choose a direction for our bishop. } 6. Be3
{ This was the big surprise for me! I had always associated Bg5 ideas involving the bishop retreat to h4! Our main provocation has been achieved and hence we shamelessly come back to e3 hoping to utilize the recently created weakening in Black's camp. }
6... O-O 7. h3 { Putting an end to any annoying Ng4/Bg4 jumps. } 7... e5
{ Black is using his superior development and the fact that his king is safe, while ours is still in the center. }
8. Qd2
{ Getting ready to castle queenside to get the king off the radar from the e-file. }
8... exd4 9. Nxd4 Re8 10. f3
{ To be honest, the h3 move doesn't fit in with our position. ..But the same can be said about his h6 which ends weakening his position and giving us crucial time to castle before Black can play d5 opening up the e-file. }
10... d5 11. O-O-O { Just in time before things could get out of hand! } 11...
Kh7 { would give us the time needed to make use of our better development. }
12. Nb3 { Pinning on the d-file and winning the d5-pawn. } *

