7... Nbd7 8. c3
{ Another strong move stabilizing the center even more! After this, our piece placement could be Nbd2, Qc2, Rfe1, and Rad1 with full control over the central affairs. Additionally White can also throw in a4 at some point to stop b5 ideas to annoy Black :@@EndBracket@@. All this guarantees a clear advantage for us. Due to White's bullet proof setup, it is hard to give Black any good advice here. }
