6. Bd3
{ As mentioned earlier, I love this bishop constructs with Bd3 & Be3 which protects the central pawns on e4 and d4 by making sure no harm can ever come to our beautiful center. }
6... O-O 7. h3
{ The final prophylactic move stopping any Bg4 or Ng4 ideas followed by O-O, Nbd2 with a stable advantage due to our mighty pawn center which can't be troubled by Black. }
7... cxd4 8. cxd4
{ Now the c3-spot is free for the development of our b1-knight. } 8... Nc6
{ Threatening to win the bishop pair with Nb4. } 9. Nc3
{ This is a much better location of our knight than d2. We can continue with O-O and Rc1 with cool play in all areas of the game! }
