{ Step 2: Develop your pieces! } 4... dxe5 5. Nxe5
{ The knight is well placed on the central square and coordinates with the rest of the pieces nicely. }
5... Be6 { Stopping Bc4 ideas. } 6. h3
{ A deep prophylactic move preventing a future Bg4. Let's try to understand what our goals are... We have the center due to which slightly more space and easier development for our pieces, So at this moment we should avoid piece exchanges, and this h3 is based on that concept! }
6... Nf6 7. c4
{ Whenever possible, it is a good idea to play c4, and only then do Nc3 which increases our space and restricts Black's pieces. }
7... Nbd7 8. Nf3
{ Keeping the center, space and avoiding exchanges and now Black has to waste some time with his bishop which is feeling out of place on e6. }
