11... Qa5 { HURRAY! Finally, the queen can't be bullied anymore! } 12. O-O
{ Now that our mobilization is almost complete, we just get the king to safety even at the cost of sacrificing the d5-pawn. Black is forced to accept our gift as he can never hope to finish his development without winning the d5-pawn. As a result, both the d-file and h1-a8 diagonal are opened to our advantage. }
12... Nbxd5 { 12...Rd8  13.Qe2  will lead to a similar fate. } 13. Nxd5
{ After this exchange, Black has to watch out for ideas involving c4. } 13...
Qxd5
{ At least exchanging the queen to reduce our attacking potential.   13...Nxd5  will be met by a cool retreat.  14.Bd2!  Gaining another tempo attacking the queen to be continued with g4 and c4 leading to a winning attack using our better-mobilized forces. }
14. Qe2
{ Sorry! We are not gonna exchange the queens after all... The idea is to play g4 followed by destruction along the d-file with Rad1 or Rfd1 and the moment we move the knight from f3 it will unleash the power of the fianchetto bishop on g2 attacking the b7-pawn. All these factors give us a decisive advantage. }
