7... O-O 8. Bh6
{ Going for the kill! Black has to be very careful not to run into a ruthless attack! }
8... Bxh6
{ A@@EndBracket@@  8...Bf5  9.O-O-O  followed by h4-h5 and mate on the h-file.   B@@EndBracket@@  8...c5  We simply avoid any counterplay with a strong central thrust.  9.d5!  followed by O-O-O and h4-h5 and mate on the h-file.   C@@EndBracket@@  8...Bg4  9.Bxg7  Kxg7  10.Ne5  followed by O-O-O and h4-h5 with a mate on the h-file...after the g4-bishop retreats :@@EndBracket@@. }
9. Qxh6
{ The queen has occupied a dangerous attacking post and Black must create some confusion to distract us from playing h4-h5 which would end badly for Black. }
9... Bg4 { Threatening to take on f3 and then d4. } 10. O-O-O
