4. d4
{ Capturing the center and taking control of the important e5-square which will prove to be an attacking hook by placing a knight there controlling Black's position. I also tried to make the exciting 4. b4 work, but it was not to be and we don't get enough compensation for the pawn. }
4... e5 { Black hopes to liquidate in the center. } 5. Nf3
{ Top priority to development! } 5... Bb4
{ Black develops with tempi attacking the knight on c3.   5...exd4  6.Nxd4  with a development advantage. }
6. Bd2 { He attacks, we protect. } 6... exd4 7. Nxd4
{ We have a stable advantage due to the better development which gives rise to annoying threats like Nd5 or Nb5. }
7... Qe5+ { Trying to ruin our coordination. } 8. Qe2
{ Endgames are welcome for us. } 8... Qxe2+ 9. Bxe2
{ We have 4 pieces developed, while Black has only one piece out. } 9... Nf6
{ Preventing Nd5 ideas. } 10. O-O-O
{ We have finished our development and can continue to increase the pressure with Rhe1 and Bf3 leading to a depressing endgame for Black. }
