{ Attacking the queen and forcing her to choose between b6 or d8 @@StartBracket@@c7 is really stupid as the battery of queen/bishop should be the other way :@@EndBracket@@@@EndBracket@@. }
15... Qb6 { Black has created a nice double attack on b2 and c3. } 16. c3
{ Protecting both d4 and b2 in one move! Black can't afford to take on b2 which would unleash our sleeping rook on a1 to the powerful 7th rank after Rb1 & Rxb7. }
16... Bc7
{ A cool retreat preparing Qd6 and Qh2 checkmate!   16...g6  can be met with  17.h6  transposing to 14...g6 lines. }
17. a4
{ I strongly feel this AlphaZero inspired thrust puts an end to the Scandinavian... }
17... O-O
{ Alex @@StartBracket@@Chessforlife@@EndBracket@@ only checks 18.f4 here.   17...a5  stopping our advance makes the b5-square very weak.  18.Qf3  with a big advantage as Black won't have any play on the queenside while our initiative on the kingside will be unstoppable. }
18. h6
{ Creating an epic pawn hook on h6 which will permanently remain a thorn in Black's flesh. }
18... g6
{ Black hopes that one day he can win the h6-pawn, but this is never going to happen :@@EndBracket@@ . }
19. a5 { Bullying the queen and asking her to leave her post on b6. } 19... Qc6
{ Black wants to prepare Nf6-e4 which is his main theme in this line.   19...Qd6  20.f4  Not allowing Qh2 checkmate :@@EndBracket@@.  20...Nf6  21.Qe2  with a clear advantage due to our influence extending to both kingside & queenside thanks to our strong rook pawns. }
20. f4 { Preventing e5 breaks and forcing Black into a passive position. }
20... Nf6
{ Black is hoping to achieve his main plan of putting the knight on e4. } 21.
Qe2 { Sending the invite to play Ne4 :@@EndBracket@@. } 21... Ne4
{ Other moves exist... but they have no plans :@@EndBracket@@.   21...b6  22.Bb5!  Forcing the queen to step away from the a8-h1 diagonal.  22...Qd6  23.axb6  Bxb6  24.Qe5!  Forcing the exchange of the queens or else get ready for a mating attack in the future.  23...Qxe5  24.fxe5  Nxg4  25.Kg2!  Although Black is a pawn up, it is not felt in this position. The bishop pair is just too dominant and the beautiful rook pawn tilts the eval in White's favor. }
22. Bxe4 { A necessary exchange. } 22... dxe4 23. c4
{ The center pawns are very strong and we have the advantage thanks to that. If Black tries to save the e4-pawn with f5, then we just go g5 creating a strong pawn hook on h6. The bishop will go to e3 to nicely blockade the e4-pawn and also support both d4/f4 pawns. Black has to sit and wait for the end! }
*

