{ This feels like a lame imitation of the Alekhine Defense :@@EndBracket@@. Black is not even threatening anything :@@EndBracket@@. That being said, 'Let's take an objective look at how to continue with White'. }
2. d4 { Capturing the center and asking Black to choose between two options. }
2... d5 { This would be the preference of Caro-Kann and Scandinavian players. }
3. exd5
{ There are many ways to get the advantage, but I feel we can brute force our way with this direct attempt at refuting the line. }
3... Qxd5 4. Nf3
{ Supporting d4 and preparing to kick the queen with c4 or Nc3 next. The knight on c6 won't feel very comfortable very soon... }
4... Bg4 5. Nc3
{ Not giving Black any breathing time to take on f3.   5...Bxf3  6.Nxd5  Bxd1  7.Nxc7+  winning the a8-rook and also ruining Black's king safety leading to a clear advantage. }
5... Qh5 { Other moves would give us the advantage without a fight. } 6. d5
{ The beginning of a forced sequence for both sides where we will eventually end up with a big advantage. }
6... O-O-O { Using the pin along the d-file to castle into safety. } 7. Be2
{ Developing the right bishop and stopping Bxf3 ideas. } 7... Bxf3
