[White "Model Games"]
[Black " Maxime Vachier Lagrave  vs. Salem Saleh, Moscow FIDE GP, 2017"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6
{ The topical reaction to the Two Knights defense. } 5. Qe2
{ The most annoying reaction to the topical line. Black has many ways to continue here, but none of them manage to equalize. }
5... Nxe4 6. Qxe4 Qd5
{ 6...Qa5  This game is a very good example of how to destroy Black's setup!  7.b4!  Gaining a nice tempo attacking the queen and the b-pawn will help us in breaking Black's queenside pawn structure with b5 in the future.  7...Qd5  8.Qe3  Not letting Black exchange the queens so easily.  8...Bf5  9.c4  Continuing to gain more momentum and improving our position by attacking the queen.  9...Qe4  10.Be2  Qxe3  Black has to take as we were threatening to play Qc3 preventing the exchange of the queens.  11.fxe3  We are happy with the opening of the f-file.  11...Nd7  12.O-O  e6  13.b5!  Going for the promised break and Black is not ready to meet this!  13...cxb5   13...c5  14.Bb2  followed by a4-a5 with a big advantage on both the kingside and the queenside.  14.Nd4!  A cool intermezzo making full use of the open f-file.  14...Bg6  15.Nxb5  Kd8  Black is forced to lose the castling rights due to the threat of Nc7 fork.  16.d4  Finally capturing the center under the most advantageous circumstances.  16...a6  17.Nc3  Bb4  18.Bd2  White was better and went on to win a good game in  @@StartBracket@@Arjun - Vaishali, Barcelona, 2021@@EndBracket@@ }
7. Qh4 { Running away from the queen exchange :@@EndBracket@@. } 7... Qe6+ 8.
Be2 Qg4 { Black is really persistent. } 9. Qg3
{ Forcing Black to improve our pawn structure once again like in the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pp2pppp/2p5/8/4Q3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/R1B1KB1R b KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6...Qa5  line. }
9... Qxg3 10. hxg3 { Now the h1 rook is feeling very good about himself. }
10... Bf5 11. b3
{ A very powerful move activating the c1-bishop via the 'Cowboy' way! The c2-pawn is immune due to d3, trapping the bishop. }
11... a5
{ 11...Nd7  12.Bb2  h6   12...e5  Black shouldn't get himself involved in any complications without fully finishing his development.  13.O-O-O  Bd6  14.d4!  Black is not ready for the opening of the position.  14...e4  15.Nd2  Nf6  16.Nc4  Bc7  17.Ne3  The knight is a cool blockader on e3.  17...Be6  18.c4  18...O-O-O  19.d5!  cxd5  20.Bxf6!  gxf6  21.cxd5±  with a clear advantage for White due to the better pawn structure in @@StartBracket@@Liang -Zherebukh, Saint Louis, 2017@@EndBracket@@.  13.O-O-O  Rg8  14.Rde1  Both the rooks are occupying the only available semi-open files.  14...a5  15.Nd4  Bg6  16.f4!  followed by f5-g4 burying the bishop on g6. @@StartBracket@@Erdos - Pantsulaia, Reykjavik, 2021@@EndBracket@@. }
12. Bb2 h6 13. O-O-O a4 14. Nd4 Bc8 15. Rde1
{ Just look at our army and compare it to Black's sleeping army :@@EndBracket@@. }
15... axb3 16. axb3
{ We have a big advantage and the only question which remains is 'How do we crash through?'. }
16... Nd7 17. Nf5 Nf6 18. g4 { The knight looks awesome on f5. } 18... Be6 19.
f4 Rg8 20. Ne3 g6 21. f5 gxf5 22. gxf5 Bd7 23. Bf3 Kd8 24. Bd4 Bg7 25. Kb2
{ Black's situation is becoming worse with every move as White is just improving while he is just sitting around doing nothing : @@EndBracket@@. }
25... Ne8 26. Bxg7 Nxg7 27. f6
{ Making sure that we have the superior pawn structure. } 27... exf6 28. Rxh6
Ne8 29. d4 Kc7 30. d5 Rg5 31. Rd1 Ra6 32. b4 Nd6
{ Black loses his patience and blunders the f6-pawn. } 33. Rxf6 cxd5 34. Rxd5
Rxd5 35. Bxd5 Nc4+ 36. Bxc4
{ Black is lost due to the fork on d5. A cool victory by MVL, showing the key themes of the Two Knights defense. }
