{ The terrifying Advance variation! } 3... c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Qb6 6. Bd3
{ Giving up the d4-pawn for the initiative with no regard to the material! }
6... cxd4 7. O-O Bd7 8. Re1 Nge7
{ 8...Rc8  9.Nbd2  Nge7  10.Nb3  Forcing Black to take on c3 and open the b-file.  10...dxc3  11.bxc3  Na5  12.Be3  Qc7  13.Nxa5  Qxa5  14.Rb1  b6  15.Qe2  Nf5  Black slips...  16.Bxf5!  exf5  17.e6!!  White opens the e-file with a brilliant pawn sacrifice.  17...Bxe6  18.Nd4  Be7  19.Bg5!!  Another brilliant piece sacrifice to destroy Black's defenses.  19...Qc5  20.Nxe6  fxe6  21.Qxe6  Rc7  22.Rbd1  The rest is just a matter of 'crushing your opponent' without giving him any chance.  22...Rd7  23.Re5  h6  24.Qg6+  Kf8  25.Qxf5+  Ke8  26.Bxe7  Rxe7  27.Rde1  A fantastic victory by White in @@StartBracket@@Kryvoruchko - Christiansen, Struga, 2021@@EndBracket@@. }
9. h4 { Adding more fuel to the fire! } 9... h6
{ 9...Rc8  10.h5  h6  11.Na3  A novel way to activate the knight!  11...a6  12.Nc2   12.Nxd4  was the move recommended in our course.  12...dxc3  13.bxc3  Na5  14.Be3  Qc7  15.Rb1!  Giving up another pawn on c3 for activity!  15...Nc4   15...Qxc3  16.Qe2  with good compensation for the pawns.  16.Bxc4  Qxc4   16...dxc4  17.Bb6±  followed by Ne3-Nd2.  17.Rxb7  Now that the rook has been activated, it is hard for Black to defend against our threats.  17...Nf5   17...Nc6  was still enough to hold the balance.  18.Nfd4  Nxe3  19.Nxe3  Qxc3  20.Nxd5!  Opening the e-file with full force!  20...exd5  21.e6  fxe6  22.Nxe6  The end is near!  22...Be7  23.Qe2  Qf6  24.Nf4  followed by Nxd5 next with a winning attack and Black resigned in @@StartBracket@@Abhimanyu - Haria@@EndBracket@@ Riga, 2021@@EndBracket@@ }
10. a3
{ Although I have recommended  10.h5  in our course, I think this is a cool alternative with the idea to prepare b4 and gain more space on the queenside. }
10... Rc8 11. b4 a6 12. Bb2 g5 13. Nh2
{ Even the comp is not able to understand this position and is constantly changing its evaluation. }
13... Bg7
{ 13...gxh4  Comp's preference.  14.Qh5  Rg8  15.Ng4  with sufficient compensation for the pawns thanks to the big weakness on f6. }
14. Ng4 gxh4 15. cxd4
{ This is a mistake, but I can only say this with an engine running, over the board, I would be completely confused.  15.Qf3  was stronger with compensation for the pawn. }
15... h5 { Black also makes an error after which we are clearly superior. } 16.
Nf6+ Bxf6 17. exf6 Ng8 18. Qf3 Rh6 19. Qxd5 Nxf6 20. Qg5 Ng4 21. Nc3 Qd8 22.
Qxd8+ Kxd8
{ Black's position is horrible due to the absence of the dark-squared bishop and the ruined pawn structure. }
23. Ne4 e5 24. f3 Nxd4 25. fxg4 hxg4 26. Ng5
{ A confusing victory by MVL :@@EndBracket@@. } *

